body_html:
I confirm this is a real issue. It was introduced in PR #15146 and it applies to both Xception and MobileNet.

However, it has been fixed since. If you upgrade to TF 1.6, you will no longer see this issue. For instance, you can pip install the TF 1.6 release candidate 1.6.0rc0 as of now.

body:
I confirm this is a real issue. It was introduced in PR https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/15146 and it applies to both Xception and MobileNet.

However, it has been fixed since. If you upgrade to TF 1.6, you will no longer see this issue. For instance, you can `pip install` the TF 1.6 release candidate `1.6.0rc0` as of now.
